Bring the family, friends and pets to celebrate our second anniversary at noon on Saturday, March 10! Taste lots of new beers, including a limited release of four aged Belgian sour ales and a special 22 oz bottle of a barrel aged dry-hopped dark rye ale.
Wurstbusters food truck will be parked out back. Come enjoy the sunshine and get a taste of what we'll be serving in our third year.

Bogtoberfest
Saturday, September 22, 2018
12:00 PM
12:00
Friday, September 28, 2018
12:00 AM
00:00
Bog Brewing Company
218 West King Street
Saint Augustine, Florida
USA
(map)
Google Calendar
ICS
Bog Brewing Company is excited to announce Bogtoberfest, an Oktoberfest celebration. A limited amount of commemorative 1-liter steins will be available for purchase and discounted stein fills will be offered throughout the week. The kickoff celebration on Saturday, Sept. 22 will also include a German-themed BBQ.
Bog will release two beers for this weeklong event:
Oktoberfest beer: Brewed true to style using 100% German malts, including Munich and Amber malts, German hops and German yeast, this 5.2% amber lager has a pleasant, toasted aroma with a satisfying maltiness.
Berliner Weisse: A low-alcohol, German-style sour beer that dates back to at least the 16th century. An abundance of wheat imparts breadiness and lactobacillus (a souring bacteria) adds a crisp tartness that makes this beer as refreshing as it is sessionable. Bogtoberfest attendees will have the option to include their choice of a traditional syrup.
The release of the Oktoberfest lager marks a special milestone for Head Brewer Steven Mendoza.
“In terms of beer styles, our first love has always been European ales, lagers and sour beers,” says Mendoza. “As The Bog has grown, we’ve been able to incorporate these more into our tap lineup. I’m really excited about this lager release because I think it is a fine example of a true German Oktoberfest. To serve it is a realization of our dream to serve world-class, European-style beer.”

10:00 PM

Google Calendar
ICS
Join us for the second annual Nights of Pints from Nov. 16 to Feb. 3! Like and follow the
Nights of Pints
Facebook page for updates.
St. Augustine breweries --
Ancient City Brewing
downtown,
Bog Brewing Company
,
Dog Rose Brewing Co.
, and
Old Coast Ales
-- will partner during the annual Nights of Lights to host the second annual Nights of Pints.
Each brewery is teaming up to create seasonal, one-of-a-kind collaboration beers that will showcase the unique beer styles of each brewmaster. Additionally, a new commemorative t-shirt design will be released on Nov. 16. With the purchase of a t-shirt ($30), brewery-goers will receive one draft beer on the house at each brewery.
Check each brewery's website for hours of operation.

Join us for St. Augustine's ultimate celebration of German-inspired lagers and ales!
For our 6th annual
#bogtoberfest
celebration, you can experience beers ranging from traditional festbiers and lagers to adventurous and unique twists on ales and sour beers.

Stay tuned for the full draft list lineup!

We're teaming up with Chef Peter from Purple Olive for a four-course dinner with five perfectly paired Bog beers on Monday, December 10 from 6 to 9 p.m.
This beer dinner at The Bog will be an intimate event on December 10. The brewery will not be open to outside guests and you must have a reservation to attend.
Purple Olive
